obo:GO_0098978  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_2437  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"N-WASP localizes to spines and functional, excitatory synapses in hippocampal neurons\"\n- Literal: \"As shown in the higher magnification images, N-WASP puncta were in close apposition to the presynaptic marker SV2, suggesting it was in postsynaptic terminals (Fig. 1A). Consistent with this, N-WASP puncta almost completely merged with the postsynaptic marker PSD-95 (Fig. 1A), indicating that N-WASP localizes to the postsynaptic side of excitatory synapses.\". Experimental description: Cell Culture and Transfection-Hippocampal low density cultures were prepared as described previously (18). Reference 18 is entitled: Rat Hippocampal Neurons in Low-density Culture (Banker, G., and Goslin, K., eds) pp. 339-370, MIT Press, Cambridge, MA\n\n8/2/2018 Pim\n- Species of overexpressed N-Wasp is not stated in the paper. Annotation was made based on the endogenous N-Wasp protein." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2437" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

